name: Rodanthe house collapses
summary: Another house on the Outer Banks of North Carolina has collapsed into the ocean, marking the 7th such collapse in the last four years. This latest incident occurred during Hurricane Ernesto, with high winds and heavy rain likely contributing to the collapse. The house was located in Rodanthe, an area that has been particularly hard-hit by coastal erosion and sea-level rise. The collapse serves as a stark reminder of the ongoing threat posed by climate change, as stronger storms and rising sea levels continue to erode the shoreline.

name: Full moon
summary: The upcoming August full moon is set to be a rare astronomical event, featuring several notable characteristics simultaneously. It will be a supermoon, meaning it will appear larger and brighter than usual due to its closer proximity to Earth. Additionally, it will be a blue moon, a term used to describe the second full moon appearing in the same calendar month. This will also be the third in a series of four consecutive supermoons, which is an unusual occurrence. As such, the full moon in August is being referred to as a "supermoon blue moon" or "Sturgeon Moon" by various news outlets.

summary: The Indianapolis Colts have made several roster moves in preparation for the upcoming season. They have claimed running back Demetric Felton off waivers from the Browns and waived Trent Pennix, who is injured. The Colts also added veteran free agents, including defensive end Germaine Pratt and linebacker Darius Leonard. In preseason action, the Colts defeated the Broncos 34-30, led by a strong performance from rookie quarterback Bo Nix. The Cardinals and Colts also faced off, with the Colts claiming the victory. Other key players who may become surprise starters include running back Hassan Haskins, linebacker Cameron Young, and safety Rodney McLeod.
